CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 23, 1966, pg. 11B reads: "At Employment Workshop At PITT - When a cross-section of Pittsburgh leadership took part in seminars and discussions on the problem of fully integrating Negroes in employment and apprenticeships pattern of the Pittsburgh area during the past three weeks, these were the scenes and principals. The sessions were sponsored by Pittsburgh corporations which have signed Vice President Humphrey's "Plans for Progress" project which stresses equal opportunity in employment...Center photo: Sarah Campbell of Homewood-Brushton Renewal Council, and delegates for the Business and Job Development Corporation, John Adams, Luther Sewell and Marty Samuels, take part in another seminar..."
TitMainTitle: Sarah Campbell, John Adams, Luther Sewell, and Marty Samuels seated behind conference table for employment workshop at University of Pittsburgh
